TextChange: Putin is disgusted by how much

Nowadays, you can't go a single day without the news of Russia invading Ukraine. Everyone has heard of the on-going issue unless you live under a rock. The threat of a world war III is on the rise. Everyone is up in arms over this problem. Personal lives, the economy, and world relations are all threatened. The thought of Russia causing a war is disheartening, but this isn't Russia's war, this is Vladimir Putins war. 
  Russia citizens do not want this war. Putin does. He wants back what was once part of Soviet Russia. With the rise of social media, you can find videos of the Russian people protesting against the war in their home country. Russian athletes and celebrities, such as Andrey Rublev, have spoken publicly about their stance and how they're against the war. Rublev, after winning his tennis match, wrote "No war please" on the camera lens for the viewers to see. Russian and Ukranian citizens have had long lived friendships. 
  Some may say that the entirety of Russia wants this war because Ukraine used to be a part of them up until 1991. Though it may be true, the vast majority outweigh the ones in favor of it. This isn't a Russian war, Putin is disgusted that the Ukranians prefer to adopt western policies. Putin is anti-democracy, which Ukraine is steeering towards. 
  This is not Russia's war, it is Putin's due to the fact that Russian citizens have made it public that they're against it.
Whatever people spend their money on brings them happiness.
